==English==
===Etymology===
From French ''[[macaque]]'' < Portuguese ''[[macaco]]'' (monkey) < Bantu.

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

#{{italbrac|racial slur}} A [[derogatory]] [[epithet]] for dark-skinned people who appear to be of Middle-Eastern descent.
#{{archaic}} {{slang}} {{italbrac|racial slur}} A dismissive epithet used by French-speaking colonials in Africa to refer to a person of North African or Subsaharan ethnicity.

